This is just my personal vim config.

Windows:

  mklink /D %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH%\vimfiles path_to_repo\vimconfig\vimfiles
  mklink /H %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH%\_vimrc path_to_repo\vimconfig\_vimrc
  mklink /H %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH%\_gvimrc path_to_repo\vimconfig\_gvimrc

N.B. I'm not 100% sure that it's correct from a Windows-perspective that I'm using %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH% instead of %USERPROFILE%, but as far as I can tell, this is what Vim actually uses for setting $HOME.

Additionally, note that the links for _vimrc and _gvimrc must be hardlinks, as Vim will overwrite symbolic links when saving files! (I'm not sure if this is a configuration error in my Vim setup.)

Mac/Unix:

  ln -s path_to_repo/vimconfig/vimfiles ~/.vim
  ln -s path_to_repo/vimconfig/_vimrc ~/.vimrc
  ln -s path_to_repo/vimconfig/_gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

